  <discussion>Limnobium spongia has two leaf forms, often on the same plant. The floating leaves have a thick layer of aerenchyma on the abaxial surface; the emersed leaves lack such tissue. Flowering and fruiting are predominantly on individuals with emersed leaves. Following pollination, the peduncle becomes recurved, forcing the developing fruit below the water surface.</discussion>
